def: Ignominy. [R. & Obs.]I blush to think upon this ignomy. Shak.
To cause to give out a slight, sharp, tinkling, sound, as bystriking metallic or other sonorous bodies together.And let me the canakin clink. Shak.
A vulture; the griffin. [Obs.]Like a white hind under the gripe's sharp claws. Shak.Gripe's egg, an alchemist's vessel. [Obs.] E. Jonson.
State of being a lion. Carlyle.
The nave of a church. Addison.
Of or pertaining to a natural order (Urticace√¶) of plants, ofwhich the nettle is the type. The order includes also the hop, theelm, the mulberry, the fig, and many other plants.
One who is lord over another or others; a superior lord; amaster. Freeman.
In the next month after the present; -- often contracted toprox.; as, on the 3d proximo.
One who believes that Christ will reign personally on earth athousand years; a Chiliast; also, a believer in the universalprevalence of Christianity for a long period.
